</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uglasya7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glasya7</A> at: 9/27/02 6:28:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1936<br> <font color=#333333>(9/27/02 7:13:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Chained versus Sustained pets...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Calebe:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Wouldn't hurt to get an upgrade to TPP with say 8 mana per tick, the same as druids and clerics are getting.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->He is a 53rd mage, did not mention epic, rods not an option.  I just mentioned what seemed to me to be the best solution at his level, and one that it seemed he was likely unaware of.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Madcazter:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  guess what the sukers at VI gave us freaking Mod rods thats the mages version of mana regen I just know thats how the lame idoits at VI will consider it<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Mod rods are negative mana, trans rods are positive mana, and yes, they are mana reneration for those mages who are high enough level to have the spell.  See <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showMessage?topicID=18.topic">Transvergence and The Complete Magician</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for how this works, for soloing, in groups, and on raids.<br>
<br>
However, at 53rd, that is not yet an option.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> BGilles:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Reclaiming pets is not the correct answer. I doubt when they built the mage class, they did it around reclaiming pets (to gain mana) and chain casting (to kill mobs). Those are tricks that have been developed by players and which IMO are not part of the mage class. They actually are hurting the mage class because now they take them into account when they make new spells / abilities.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Perhaps.  But <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> had a great opportunity to reduce the appeal of chaining pets when they dramaticly increased the strength of pets.<br>
<br>
As I argued in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=82.topic">Increased Pet Strength, Summary Pro and Con</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, one problem with making pets innately stronger is that it encourages pet chaining, which I saw, like you, as limiting class upgrades.  For that reason, I argued that adding pet strength through buffs and summoned items was a better all around solution.  Although summoned armor and focus items do make prepared pets a little stronger, as does lifting the pet haste cap, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> chose to make elementals innately stronger.  Further, the class AAs <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental Pact</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Reclaim Energy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in my mind confirm that chaining and cannibalizing pets are now an accepted part of the design of the mage class.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> BGilles:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I think the way they desined the mage class is:<br>
Keep your pet alive as long as possible<br>
Meditate to regen mana<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->For good or ill, this appears to be more of a beastlord specialty now, as they have much better pet buffs and heals, and chaining warders is impossible.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Abuser of EZCodes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 625<br> <font color=#333333>(9/27/02 9:21:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chained versus Sustained pets...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I doubt when they built the mage class, they did it around reclaiming pets (to gain mana) and chain casting (to kill mobs). Those are tricks that have been developed by players and which IMO are not part of the mage class.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You didn't think I would let this one go unanswered, did you?  I remember a time when magicians having easy access to right click items with Reclaim Energy was the big joke of Norrath.  What possible use would a spell like this be when at most levels, you don't get very much mana at all?  The only exception, of course, was reclaiming the 49 Earth pet (and later the MS 2 pet).  Even that wasn't spectacular until Luclin, where skills and focus effects dramatically improved the usefulness of the &quot;joke&quot; spell of the Magician class.<br>
<br>
    Chain casting should not be part of the magician class?  Consider that the only &quot;trick&quot; involved in chain summoning involves issuing a pet command while casting.  With two magicians the need to use a pet command while casting is obviated, and allows both magicians to be much more mana efficient.  The summoning cost of pets is quite inexpensive, and we happen to have the least mana intensive pet summons in the game, made even MORE efficient with Luclin.<br>
<br>
    Now let's focus for a moment on the Magician Class skills.  We have Quick Summoning (faster cast time on pets and other summons, making chaining safer than ever), Elemental Pact (The dirt cheap gems become even cheaper, and cease to be a limiting factor on chain casting or pet canni), and of course Improved Reclaim (making the &quot;joke&quot; spell of Norrath incredibly useful after all, and allowing us to chain pets WITHOUT issuing a pet command while casting, mana free.)<br>
<br>
Like it or not, they are legitimite tactics, and are part of the Magician class.  Magicians technically coerce and command elementals as melee tools in combat.  We may as well play them as such. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulobaner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lobaner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(9/27/02 10:10:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chained versus Sustained pets...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Magicians technically coerce and command elementals as melee tools in combat. We may as well play them as such.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Mister, I do not like the sound of that at all!<br>
<br>
Chaining and cannibalizing elementals is a barbaric and demeaning practice!<br>
<br>
That other fellow is right.  Equip and sustain an elemental as long as you can.  If that means a few more minutes pressing your butt cheeks into the sand, well so be it!<br>
<br>
I'm keeping an eye on you....<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Lobaner</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uconjem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Conjem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(9/27/02 10:17:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chained versus Sustained pets...</span><hr size=1> Reclaim a dying pet.  Summon a new one.  Use quested armor to give 60 percent haste to fresh pet and have a net increase in mana.  Total time around 30 seconds.  Sit and med.  With a fresh pet you do damage even when OOM.  <br>
<br>
